{"id": "7212cca9be971997434c2b3a27411a163bbd89c3", "content": {"title": "Better Intermediates Improve CTC Inference", "abstract": "This paper proposes a method for improved CTC inference with searched intermediates and multi-pass conditioning. The paper \ufb01rst formulates self-conditioned CTC as a probabilistic model with an intermediate prediction as a latent representation and provides a tractable conditioning framework. We then propose two new conditioning methods based on the new formulation: (1) Searched intermediate conditioning that re\ufb01nes intermediate predictions with beam-search, (2) Multi-pass conditioning that uses predictions of previous inference for conditioning the next inference. These new approaches enable better conditioning than the original self-conditioned CTC during inference and improve the \ufb01nal performance. Experiments with the LibriSpeech dataset show relative 3%/12% performance improvement at the maximum in test clean/other sets compared to the original self-conditioned CTC.", "year": 2022, "ssId": "7212cca9be971997434c2b3a27411a163bbd89c3", "arXivId": "2204.00176", "link": "https://arxiv.org/pdf/2204.00176.pdf", "openAccess": true, "authors": ["Tatsuya Komatsu", "Yusuke Fujita", "Jaesong Lee", "Lukas Lee", "Shinji Watanabe", "Yusuke Kida"], "text": {"better": 10, "intermediates": 4, "improve": 5, "ctc": 56, "inference": 26, "tatsuya": 2, "komatsu": 4, "yusuke": 2, "fujita": 2, "jaesong": 1, "lee": 6, "lukas": 1, "shinji": 1, "watanabe": 9, "kida": 1, "line": 1, "corporation": 2, "naver": 1, "carnegie": 1, "mellon": 1, "university": 1, "linecorp": 1, "com": 1, "arxiv": 4, "cs": 1, "cl": 1, "apr": 1, "abstract": 1, "paper": 7, "proposes": 1, "method": 12, "improved": 6, "searched": 10, "multi": 10, "pass": 19, "conditioning": 56, "formulates": 1, "self": 23, "conditioned": 21, "probabilistic": 6, "model": 19, "intermediate": 36, "prediction": 18, "latent": 6, "representation": 12, "provides": 2, "tractable": 3, "framework": 2, "p